text: John Andrew Koskinen (born June 30, 1939) is an American businessman and politician. He was the non-executive chairman of Freddie Mac from September 2008 to December 2011. He was the Commissioner of Internal Revenue from 2013 to 2017. ==References== Category:1939 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from Cleveland Category:Businesspeople from Cleveland Category:Democratic Party (United States) politicians Category:Commissioners of Internal Revenue
